# Database migrations

Migrations use [Alembic](https://alembic.sqlalchemy.org/) with async PostgreSQL.

## Filename format

Configured in `alembic.ini`:

```
YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS_<revision>_<slug>.py
```

Example: `20260517_021252_c343d3e8e3b5_initial_schema.py`

## Commands

```bash
cd backend

# Apply all pending migrations
uv run alembic upgrade head

# Create a new migration (after editing models)
uv run alembic revision --autogenerate -m "add_some_column"
uv run alembic upgrade head

# Roll back one revision
uv run alembic downgrade -1

# Show current revision
uv run alembic current
```

Shortcut: `uv run db-migrate` (same as `alembic upgrade head`).

Database URL is read from `backend/.env` (`DB_*` variables).
